## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- npm or yarn

### Installation

1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/prioritization-tool.git
cd prioritization-tool
```

2. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

3. Start the development server
```bash
npm start
```

4. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser

## How to Use

### Screen 1: Input Tasks
- Type a task name and click "Add" (or press Enter)
- Add as many tasks as you need
- Optionally bulk import multiple tasks by pasting them line-by-line
- Click "Rank Tasks" to proceed

### Screen 2: Rank Each Task
- For each task, select one option from each criterion
- All four criteria must be selected before proceeding
- Progress bar shows your position
- Click "Next Task" to continue (or "See Results" on the last task)

